text.__SUMMARY__: Habenaria obovata is a species of plant in the family Orchidaceae. It is endemic to Cameroon. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical dry lowland grassland.
text.Sources: Cheek, M. & Cable, S. (2000). "Habenaria obovata". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 2000: e.T39579A10242017. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.2000.RLTS.T39579A10242017.en. Retrieved 19 December 2017.
